Summary 
Project Overview 
The Library Management System is a console-based C program designed to help 
manage books in a library. 
It performs essential operations such as adding, viewing, searching, modifying, 
deleting, issuing, and returning books, and stores all data permanently in binary files. 
This project demonstrates file handling, structures, user input validation, and menu
driven programming in C. 
Objectives 
To automate library record management. 
To efficiently track books, issues, and returns. 
To demonstrate practical use of file I/O and data structures in C. 
To provide a learning-level example of a real-world management system. 
